Why do institutional investors shy away from Crypto

- Most clients are pension funds
- Many avoid it because the size of the market is too small - min investment is 120m and it would be levered up on that too.
- Futures account primarily targeted at commodity markets and etfs.


- Possible to externally invest in external managed accounts via Hedge Funds